{
  "info": {
    "name": "Learnova Video Service",
    "description": "Complete API collection for the Learnova Video Processing Microservice.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this **collection** into Postman\n2. Import the **environment** file: `Learnova_Video_Service.postman_environment.json`\n3. Select the **\"Learnova Video Service — Local\"** environment from the top-right dropdown\n4. Set the `service_secret` environment variable to match your `SERVICE_AUTH_SECRET` from `.env`\n5. The collection pre-request script auto-generates the `service_token` JWT before each request\n\n## Testing Flow\n1. **Health Check** → verify all services are up\n2. **Create Upload URL** → get presigned URL + videoId\n3. **Upload Video to MinIO** → PUT file directly to the presigned URL\n4. **Trigger Processing** → start transcoding\n5. **Get Video by ID** → poll until status is READY\n6. **Play Video** → open `stream_url` in HLS player\n\n## Environment Variables\n| Variable | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `base_url` | Video service URL (default: http://localhost:4001) |\n| `minio_url` | MinIO API URL (default: http://localhost:9000) |\n| `service_secret` | Shared secret matching SERVICE_AUTH_SECRET |\n| `service_name` | Name sent in JWT payload |\n| `service_token` | Auto-generated JWT (set by pre-request script) |\n| `video_id` | Auto-saved from upload-url response |\n| `upload_url` | Auto-saved presigned URL for MinIO |\n| `stream_url` | Auto-saved HLS master playlist URL |\n| `thumbnail_url` | Auto-saved thumbnail URL |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{service_token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "const secret = pm.environment.get('service_secret');",
          "if (!secret) {",
          "  console.warn('service_secret not set — select the Learnova Video Service environment');",
          "  return;",
          "}",
          "",
          "const serviceName = pm.environment.get('service_name') || 'learnova-server';",
          "",
          "const header = btoa(JSON.stringify({ alg: 'HS256', typ: 'JWT' })).replace(/=/g, '');",
          "const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);",
          "const payload = btoa(JSON.stringify({",
          "  service: serviceName,",
          "  iat: now,",
          "  exp: now + 3600",
          "})).replace(/=/g, '');",
          "",
          "const signInput = header + '.' + payload;",
          "const signature = CryptoJS.HmacSHA256(signInput, secret);",
          "const sigBase64 = CryptoJS.enc.Base64.stringify(signature)",
          "  .replace(/\\+/g, '-').replace(/\\//g, '_').replace(/=/g, '');",
          "",
          "const token = signInput + '.' + sigBase64;",
          "pm.environment.set('service_token', token);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0. Health Check",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Check if all dependencies (PostgreSQL, Redis, MinIO) are healthy.\n\n**No authentication required.**\n\n**Expected Response (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"healthy\",\n  \"service\": \"video-service\",\n  \"checks\": {\n    \"database\": \"ok\",\n    \"redis\": \"ok\",\n    \"minio\": \"ok\"\n  },\n  \"uptime\": 12.345\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('All checks pass', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body.status).to.eql('healthy');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.checks.database).to.eql('ok');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.checks.redis).to.eql('ok');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.checks.minio).to.eql('ok');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "1. Direct Upload (Recommended)",
      "description": "Single-request upload: POST the video file and the service handles storage + processing automatically.\n\nThis is the simplest way to upload a video.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Upload Video (auto-process)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "video",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "",
                  "description": "Select a video file (.mp4, .mov, .webm, .avi, .mkv)"
                },
                {
                  "key": "autoProcess",
                  "value": "true",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Set to 'false' to upload without triggering transcoding"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/videos/upload",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "videos", "upload"]
            },
            "description": "Upload a video file directly. The service stores it in MinIO and auto-starts transcoding.\n\n**How to use in Postman:**\n1. Go to the **Body** tab → **form-data** is already selected\n2. On the `video` row, click **Select Files** → pick your `.mp4` file\n3. Hit **Send**\n\n**Form fields:**\n| Key | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `video` | file | Yes | The video file |\n| `autoProcess` | text | No | `true` (default) to auto-start transcoding, `false` to only upload |\n| `callbackUrl` | text | No | Webhook URL for completion notification |\n\n**Response (201):**\n```json\n{\n  \"message\": \"Video uploaded and processing started\",\n  \"videoId\": \"uuid-here\",\n  \"status\": \"UPLOADED\",\n  \"originalName\": \"my-lecture.mp4\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n**Next:** Poll \"Get Video by ID\" until status is `READY`."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Has videoId', () => pm.expect(body.videoId).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "pm.test('Has message', () => pm.expect(body.message).to.include('uploaded'));",
                  "",
                  "pm.environment.set('video_id', body.videoId);",
                  "",
                  "console.log('Video ID:', body.videoId);",
                  "console.log('Status:', body.status);",
                  "console.log('Message:', body.message);",
                  "console.log('Next: Poll Get Video by ID until status is READY');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Upload Video (no auto-process)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "video",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "",
                  "description": "Select a video file"
                },
                {
                  "key": "autoProcess",
                  "value": "false",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/videos/upload",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "videos", "upload"]
            },
            "description": "Upload a video without auto-processing. You can trigger processing later via `POST /api/videos/:videoId/process`."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.environment.set('video_id', body.videoId);",
                  "",
                  "console.log('Video ID:', body.videoId);",
                  "console.log('Status:', body.status);",
                  "console.log('Upload only — trigger processing manually when ready');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Presigned URL Flow (Advanced)",
      "description": "Alternative 3-step flow for large files — the client uploads directly to MinIO bypassing the Node.js server.\n\nStep 1 auto-saves `video_id` and `upload_url` to the environment.\nStep 2 uses the saved `upload_url` to upload directly to MinIO.\nStep 3 triggers the transcoding pipeline.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Step 1 — Create Upload URL",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"originalName\": \"sample-lecture.mp4\",\n  \"mimeType\": \"video/mp4\",\n  \"fileSize\": 10485760\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/videos/upload-url",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "videos", "upload-url"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a video record (status: UPLOADING) and returns a presigned PUT URL for MinIO.\n\n**Request Body:**\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `originalName` | string | Yes | Original filename |\n| `mimeType` | string | Yes | video/mp4, video/quicktime, video/webm, video/x-msvideo, video/x-matroska |\n| `fileSize` | number | Yes | Size in bytes (max 5 GB) |\n| `callbackUrl` | string | No | Webhook URL for completion notification |\n\n**Response (201):**\n```json\n{\n  \"videoId\": \"uuid-here\",\n  \"uploadUrl\": \"http://localhost:9000/video-raw/uploads/uuid/original.mp4?X-Amz-...\",\n  \"rawKey\": \"uploads/uuid/original.mp4\"\n}\n```\n\n**Auto-saves to environment:** `video_id`, `upload_url`"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has videoId', () => pm.expect(body.videoId).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "pm.test('Response has uploadUrl', () => pm.expect(body.uploadUrl).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "pm.test('Response has rawKey', () => pm.expect(body.rawKey).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "",
                  "pm.environment.set('video_id', body.videoId);",
                  "pm.environment.set('upload_url', body.uploadUrl);",
                  "",
                  "console.log('✅ Saved video_id:', body.videoId);",
                  "console.log('✅ Saved upload_url (use in Step 2)');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 2 — Upload Video to MinIO",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "video/mp4"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "file",
              "file": {
                "src": ""
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{upload_url}}",
              "host": ["{{upload_url}}"]
            },
            "description": "Upload the video file directly to MinIO using the presigned URL from Step 1.\n\n**Auth:** None needed — presigned URL has credentials in query params.\n\n**How to use in Postman:**\n1. Go to the **Body** tab\n2. Select **binary**\n3. Click **Select File** → pick your `.mp4` file\n4. Hit **Send**\n\n**Expected:** `200 OK` (empty body)"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const url = pm.environment.get('upload_url');",
                  "if (!url) {",
                  "  console.error('❌ upload_url is empty — run Step 1 first');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Upload successful (200)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "console.log('✅ Video uploaded to MinIO — proceed to Step 3');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 3 — Trigger Processing",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/videos/{{video_id}}/process",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "videos", "{{video_id}}", "process"]
            },
            "description": "Triggers the transcoding pipeline for the uploaded video.\n\nThe worker will:\n1. Download raw video from MinIO\n2. Extract duration via ffprobe\n3. Generate a thumbnail at 10% mark\n4. Transcode to HLS at 360p, 480p, 720p, 1080p\n5. Upload all segments to MinIO `video-processed` bucket\n6. Send webhook to `callbackUrl`\n\n**Optional body:**\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `callbackUrl` | string | Override the default webhook URL |\n\n**Response (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"message\": \"Processing started\",\n  \"videoId\": \"uuid-here\"\n}\n```\n\n**Next:** Poll \"Get Video by ID\" until status is `READY`."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const id = pm.environment.get('video_id');",
                  "if (!id) {",
                  "  console.error('❌ video_id is empty — run Step 1 first');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Processing started', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.eql('Processing started');",
                  "});",
                  "console.log('✅ Processing queued — poll Get Video by ID until status is READY');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Video Management",
      "description": "CRUD operations on videos. Most requests use the `video_id` saved from the Upload Flow.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Video by ID (Poll Status)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/videos/{{video_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "videos", "{{video_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Fetch full metadata for a video. **Use this to poll status after triggering processing.**\n\nStatus transitions: `UPLOADING → UPLOADED → PROCESSING → READY` (or `FAILED`)\n\nWhen `READY`, the test script auto-saves `stream_url` and `thumbnail_url` to the environment.\n\n**Response (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"videoId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"status\": \"READY\",\n  \"duration\": 125.5,\n  \"thumbnailUrl\": \"http://localhost:9000/video-processed/processed/uuid/thumbnail.jpg\",\n  \"streamUrl\": \"http://localhost:9000/video-processed/processed/uuid/hls/master.m3u8\",\n  \"resolutions\": {\n    \"360p\": \"processed/uuid/hls/360p/playlist.m3u8\",\n    \"480p\": \"processed/uuid/hls/480p/playlist.m3u8\",\n    \"720p\": \"processed/uuid/hls/720p/playlist.m3u8\",\n    \"1080p\": \"processed/uuid/hls/1080p/playlist.m3u8\"\n  },\n  \"originalName\": \"sample-lecture.mp4\",\n  \"mimeType\": \"video/mp4\",\n  \"fileSize\": \"10485760\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-21T...\",\n  \"processedAt\": \"2026-03-21T...\"\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Has videoId', () => pm.expect(body.videoId).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "pm.test('Has valid status', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(body.status).to.be.oneOf(['UPLOADING','UPLOADED','PROCESSING','READY','FAILED']);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (body.status === 'READY') {",
                  "  pm.test('Has streamUrl', () => pm.expect(body.streamUrl).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "  pm.test('Has thumbnailUrl', () => pm.expect(body.thumbnailUrl).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "  pm.test('Has duration', () => pm.expect(body.duration).to.be.a('number'));",
                  "  pm.test('Has resolutions', () => pm.expect(body.resolutions).to.be.an('object'));",
                  "",
                  "  pm.environment.set('stream_url', body.streamUrl);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('thumbnail_url', body.thumbnailUrl);",
                  "",
                  "  console.log('🎬 Stream URL:', body.streamUrl);",
                  "  console.log('🖼️ Thumbnail:', body.thumbnailUrl);",
                  "  console.log('⏱️ Duration:', body.duration, 'seconds');",
                  "} else if (body.status === 'FAILED') {",
                  "  console.error('❌ Processing failed:', body.errorMessage);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.log('⏳ Status:', body.status, '— send this request again to poll');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List All Videos",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/videos?page=1&limit=20",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
