    {
      "name": "4. Playback",
      "description": "Use these after a video reaches READY status to verify streaming and thumbnails.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get HLS Master Playlist",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{stream_url}}",
              "host": ["{{stream_url}}"]
            },
            "description": "Fetch the HLS master `.m3u8` playlist directly from MinIO.\n\nThis is the URL you'd pass to an HLS player (hls.js, Video.js, VLC).\n\nThe `stream_url` is auto-saved when you run \"Get Video by ID\" and the video is READY.\n\n**Test playback:**\n- Open https://hlsjs.video-dev.org/demo/ and paste this URL\n- Or open in VLC: File → Open Network Stream\n\n**Expected:** Returns an `.m3u8` playlist text like:\n```\n#EXTM3U\n#EXT-X-VERSION:3\n#EXT-X-STREAM-INF:BANDWIDTH=800000,RESOLUTION=640x360\n360p/playlist.m3u8\n...\n```"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const url = pm.environment.get('stream_url');",
                  "if (!url) {",
                  "  console.error('❌ stream_url is empty — run Get Video by ID first (video must be READY)');",
                  "}"
